for sanitary waste require that the concentration of chlorine be maintained as close to 1 milligrams/liter as possible
in discharges from facilities housing ten or more persons. For facilities continuously staffed by nine or fewer persons
or only intermittently staffed by any number of persons, the BPT guideline for sanitary waste require no discharge
of floating solids. A ``no floating solids'' guideline also applies to domestic waste.



